reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Adorable, Fun, Perfect Size & Durable, Good Quality & Value For Babies, Toddlers & Kids..
reviews.reviewText: My son has recently become interested and obsessed with nesting dolls. I had ordered him a couple, they were wood, and a few of the pieces ended up breaking or cracking. He can be a little rough on his toys-he plays hard and with a lot of passion. But when I found these and saw that they’re all silicone, I knew it would be perfect for him. This nesting doll set is good quality, well made- perfect size for little hands and easy for toddlers and little ones to play with. And because of their silicone material-they are extremely durable and study. If thrown, they actually bounce. And it’s super easy to clean the parts, if needed. But kids love this, it looks cute and it’s a good value for its price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Difficult to pull apart and put back together
reviews.reviewText: This is not little people friendly who are just learning fine motor skills. It’s very challenging for my 2 year old to take this apart and he has not been successful at putting it back together. He loves staking dolls and plays with wooden ones I was hoping these would be better but I’m disappointed. I also didn’t realize how much dirt and grime sticks to silicone.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fun for any age
reviews.reviewText: We had some family come to town and one of our nieces ended up playing with these nesting dolls for two hours... They are very soft and bendable. It is near impossible to injury oneself with these unless you throw it at someone like a baseball (don't ask how I know). The colors are really nice and they go together and come apart with ease. They fit into each other and have an almost "locking" feel. The texture is very soft yet give you good grip.Be mindful of the small piece around young kids as it can be a choking hazard.
